commit.message:
Implement C main

Call fuse_daemonize from C main, so that the OCaml runtime doesn't see
the fork call so that resetting the domain locks is no more necessary.
Remove direct call to caml_atfork_hook

Format C files

Format C files with clang-format

Use the internal atfork hook

Call caml_atfork_hook instead of caml_reset_domain_lock/caml_acquire_domain_lock
fchdir with error handling

Reinitialize child locks after fuse_setup

fuse_setup calls fork, so the domain locks must
be reinitialized in the child process.

Rename domain lock functions

caml_enter_blocking_section -> caml_release_runtime_system
caml_leave_blocking_section -> caml_acquire_runtime_system
Update README

Fix deadlocks

Replace caml_release_runtime_system and caml_acquire_runtime_system with
caml_leave_blocking_section and caml_enter_blocking_section.
Replace 'opam config var' with 'opam var'
